Class Node

  • java.lang.Object
    • kodkod.ast.Node
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    Decls, Expression, Formula, IntExpression

    public abstract class Node
extends Object
    A node in the abstract syntax tree (DAG). A node can accept a ReturnVisitor and have a sequence of zero or more children.
    Author:
    Emina Torlak
    Specfields:
    children: int ->lone Node
    components: set Node
    Invariants:
    children.Node = { i: int | 0 <= i < #children }
    components= children[int]
